      "text": "# Goal\n\nProduce a design for a production-lite version of the data platform components needed to support one or more of the following use cases, and implement an end to end\niteration of that design(s). Both the design and code will be reviewed as part of a follow-up interview to simulate the normal Kontaktio code and design review\nprocesses.\n\n\n## Performant, Reliable, Secure Real Time Writes\n### Solution Requirements\nHandle 1 million writes per minute (~20kb of data per request) with de-duplication\nLess than 2-5 second end to end ingest latency (from ingest to data being queryable)\nAbility to perform on the fly de-identification of data (write ePHI data to separate tables / environment)\n\nExample if new Patient record\nPatient Record\n        Name\n        DOB\n        Favorite Color\nCreate two records\n        -> PHI Patient Record\n                        PHI Record ID\n                        Name\n                        DOB\n                        Favorite Color\n        -> De-identified Patient Record\n                Obfuscated id which is a reference to PHI Patient Record\n                Favorite Color\n\n## Scoring Rubric (Take Home Portion)\n(0 low - 5 high)\n\nDesign is cohesive\nDesign is modular\nDocumentation for how to build, test and run code is valid (i.e. following docs results in code that builds, passes tests, and runs with expected functionality locally or\nwhen deployed to a remote environment)\nDemo & prototype code demonstrates a worked example of all interfaces of the production design (e.g. data ingest, data transforms and data query) with simplified or\nmock implementations of core components based on time constraints\n1 or more core components of the system has automated tests / validation scripts\n\nOutputs\n Diagrams & documents for your design\n Source code (link to github/bitbucket or zip file) for the implemented iteration of that design\n If AI Coding Agents were used (strongly encouraged!), please provide the plans that were created by the AI Coding Agent (e.g. raw copy of prompts and plan outputs\n(not code) saved in a single file or zipped folder)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "# Goal\n\nProduce a design for a production-lite version of the data platform components needed to support one or more of the following use cases, and implement an end to end iteration of that design(s). Both the design and code will be reviewed as part of a follow-up interview to simulate the normal Kontaktio code and design review processes.\n\n\n## Performant, Reliable, Secure Real Time Writes\n### Solution Requirements\nHandle 1 million writes per minute (~20kb of data per request) with de-duplication\nLess than 2-5 second end to end ingest latency (from ingest to data being queryable)\nAbility to perform on the fly de-identification of data (write ePHI data to separate tables / environment)\n\nExample if new Patient record\nPatient Record\n        Name\n        DOB\n        Favorite Color\nCreate two records\n        -> PHI Patient Record\n                        PHI Record ID\n                        Name\n                        DOB\n                        Favorite Color\n        -> De-identified Patient Record\n                Obfuscated id which is a reference to PHI Patient Record\n                Favorite Color\n\n## Scoring Rubric (Take Home Portion)\n(0 low - 5 high)\n\nDesign is cohesive\nDesign is modular\nDocumentation for how to build, test and run code is valid (i.e. following docs results in code that builds, passes tests, and runs with expected functionality locally or when deployed to a remote environment)\nDemo & prototype code demonstrates a worked example of all interfaces of the production design (e.g. data ingest, data transforms and data query) with simplified or mock implementations of core components based on time constraints\n1 or more core components of the system has automated tests / validation scripts\n\nOutputs\n Diagrams & documents for your design\n Source code (link to github/bitbucket or zip file) for the implemented iteration of that design\n If AI Coding Agents were used (strongly encouraged!), please provide the plans that were created by the AI Coding Agent (e.g. raw copy of prompts and plan outputs (not code) saved in a single file or zipped folder)",
